<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Group-By on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/group-by/</link><description>Recent content in Group-By on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/group-by/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] SQL GROUP BY / Aggregate Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/aggregate-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/aggregate-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-group-by--aggregate-error-fix"&gt;SQL GROUP BY / Aggregate Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a SELECT query mixes aggregated columns (SUM, COUNT, AVG) with non-aggregated columns without a GROUP BY clause. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;In aggregated query without GROUP BY, expression #X of SELECT list contains nonaggregated column&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you use an aggregate function alongside regular columns, the database needs to know how to group the non-aggregated values. Without GROUP BY, the result is ambiguous — which row&amp;rsquo;s value should be returned for the non-aggregated column?&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL GROUP BY Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-group-by-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-group-by-error/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a SELECT statement includes a column that is neither aggregated nor included in the GROUP BY clause. The message reads: &lt;code&gt;Expression not in GROUP BY clause&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When using GROUP BY, every non-aggregated column in SELECT must appear in the GROUP BY clause. MySQL&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/code&gt; mode enforces this ANSI SQL standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SELECT includes columns not in GROUP BY or aggregate function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;SELECT *&lt;/code&gt; with GROUP BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing GROUP BY for aggregate queries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;sql_mode=ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-add-all-non-aggregated-columns-to-group-by"&gt;Fix 1: Add all non-aggregated columns to GROUP BY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department, name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-aggregate-functions"&gt;Fix 2: Use aggregate functions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Get one name per department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;MAX&lt;/span&gt;(name) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; sample_name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-any_value-for-non-deterministic-columns"&gt;Fix 3: Use ANY_VALUE for non-deterministic columns&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, ANY_VALUE(name), &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; user_id, created_at, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; user_id;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1055: Expression not in GROUP BY clause
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-grouping.md"&gt;No GROUP BY Expression&lt;/a&gt; — related GROUP BY issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-unknown-column-orderby.md"&gt;Unknown Column in ORDER BY&lt;/a&gt; — ORDER BY references non-grouped column&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL HAVING Clause Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-no-having/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-no-having/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when the HAVING clause references columns that are not in the GROUP BY clause or inside aggregate functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HAVING filters groups after GROUP BY is applied. Like SELECT with GROUP BY, HAVING can only reference grouped columns or aggregate expressions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HAVING references a column not in GROUP BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HAVING uses a column without aggregate function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confusing WHERE and HAVING usage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-aggregate-functions-in-having"&gt;Fix 1: Use aggregate functions in HAVING&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; department &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Engineering&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-where-for-pre-aggregation-filtering"&gt;Fix 2: Use WHERE for pre-aggregation filtering&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Filter BEFORE grouping — use WHERE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; status &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;active&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-include-column-in-group-by"&gt;Fix 3: Include column in GROUP BY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, status, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department, status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; status &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;active&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; user_id, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SUM&lt;/span&gt;(amount)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; user_id
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; created_at &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;2024-01-01&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1055: Not a GROUP BY expression in HAVING
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="group-by-error.md"&gt;GROUP BY Error&lt;/a&gt; — SELECT not grouped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-grouping.md"&gt;No Grouping&lt;/a&gt; — related GROUP BY issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Not a GROUP BY Clause Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-no-orderby/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-no-orderby/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when ORDER BY or HAVING clauses reference columns that are not part of the GROUP BY clause or aggregate functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After GROUP BY is applied, only grouped columns and aggregates are available. Referencing other columns in ORDER BY or HAVING violates this constraint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ORDER BY references a column not in SELECT or GROUP BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HAVING clause uses a non-aggregated column&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect GROUP BY placement in the query&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-order-by-grouped-or-aggregated-columns"&gt;Fix 1: Order by grouped or aggregated columns&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; employee_name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-column-aliases-in-order-by"&gt;Fix 2: Use column aliases in ORDER BY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; dept_count
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; dept_count &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-fix-having-to-use-aggregates"&gt;Fix 3: Fix HAVING to use aggregates&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; department &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Engineering&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;HAVING&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; user_id, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SUM&lt;/span&gt;(amount)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; user_id
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; created_at;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1055: Not a GROUP BY clause
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="group-by-error.md"&gt;GROUP BY Error&lt;/a&gt; — SELECT not grouped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="sql-unknown-column-orderby.md"&gt;Unknown Column ORDER BY&lt;/a&gt; — column doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Not a GROUP BY Expression Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-group-by-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-group-by-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sql-not-a-group-by-expression-error-fix"&gt;SQL Not a GROUP BY Expression Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A SQL GROUP BY error occurs when a SELECT column is neither included in the GROUP BY clause nor wrapped in an aggregate function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When using GROUP BY, every column in SELECT must either be in the GROUP BY clause or used within an aggregate function (COUNT, SUM, AVG, etc.). Non-grouped columns have ambiguous values for each group.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Not a GROUP BY Expression Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-no-grouping/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-no-grouping/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a column in the SELECT list is neither part of the GROUP BY clause nor wrapped in an aggregate function. It is a variant of the GROUP BY error.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With &lt;code&gt;ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/code&gt; mode, every column in SELECT must either appear in GROUP BY or be used inside an aggregate function like COUNT, SUM, MAX, MIN, or AVG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SELECT includes a raw column without grouping by it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;SELECT *&lt;/code&gt; with GROUP BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mixing aggregated and non-aggregated data incorrectly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-include-the-column-in-group-by"&gt;Fix 1: Include the column in GROUP BY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, employee_name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Correct
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, employee_name, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department, employee_name;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-an-aggregate-function"&gt;Fix 2: Use an aggregate function&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;MAX&lt;/span&gt;(employee_name), &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-any_value"&gt;Fix 3: Use ANY_VALUE&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; department, ANY_VALUE(employee_name), &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; employees
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; department;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; category, title, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;COUNT&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; products
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;GROUP&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; category;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1055: Not a GROUP BY expression
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="group-by-error.md"&gt;GROUP BY Error&lt;/a&gt; — related GROUP BY issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="no-grouping.md"&gt;No GROUP BY&lt;/a&gt; — missing GROUP BY clause&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQL Unknown Column in ORDER BY Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-unknown-column-orderby/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/sql/sql-unknown-column-orderby/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when the ORDER BY clause references a column that does not exist or is not available in the current query context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The database cannot find the column specified in the ORDER BY clause. This can happen when the column doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist, or when using GROUP BY and the column is not in SELECT or GROUP BY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column name misspelled in ORDER BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column not in SELECT list when using ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ordering by alias that wasn&amp;rsquo;t defined&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Column from a table not in the FROM clause&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-verify-the-column-exists"&gt;Fix 1: Verify the column exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Check available columns
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SHOW&lt;/span&gt; COLUMNS &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Use correct column name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; orders &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; created_at &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-order-by-column-alias"&gt;Fix 2: Order by column alias&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; name, price &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; quantity &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; total
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; order_items
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; total &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-order-by-column-position"&gt;Fix 3: Order by column position&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; name, price, quantity
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; order_items
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DESC&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- orders by the 3rd column (quantity)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; id, name &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ORDER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;BY&lt;/span&gt; email;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ERROR 1054: Unknown column &amp;#39;email&amp;#39; in &amp;#39;order clause&amp;#39;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="column-not-found.md"&gt;Column Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — column doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="group-by-error.md"&gt;GROUP BY Error&lt;/a&gt; — GROUP BY related issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>